#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an7.72:14.1"
msgid "“Ārocayāmi vo, bhikkhave, paṭivedayāmi vo, bhikkhave, yathā etadeva tassa varaṃ dussīlassa … pe … kasambujātassa yaṃ balavā puriso sīse vā gahetvā khandhe vā gahetvā tattaṃ ayomañcaṃ vā ayopīṭhaṃ vā abhinisīdāpeyya vā abhinipajjāpeyya vā. "
msgstr "“I declare this to you, mendicants, I announce this to you! It would be better for that unethical man to have a strong man grab him by the head or shoulders and make him sit or lie down on a red-hot iron bed or seat. "

msgctxt "an7.72:14.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an7.72:14.3"
msgid "Tatonidānañhi so, bhikkhave, maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ, na tveva tappaccayā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya. "
msgstr "Because that might result in death or deadly pain. But when his body breaks up, after death, it would not cause him to be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

msgctxt "an7.72:14.4"
msgid "Yañca kho so, bhikkhave, dussīlo pāpadhammo … pe … kasambujāto khattiyamahāsālānaṃ vā brāhmaṇamahāsālānaṃ vā gahapatimahāsālānaṃ vā saddhādeyyaṃ mañcapīṭhaṃ paribhuñjati. Tañhi tassa, bhikkhave, hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati. (6) "
msgstr "But when such an unethical man enjoys the use of beds and seats given in faith by well-to-do aristocrats or brahmins or householders, that brings him lasting harm and suffering. When his body breaks up, after death, he’s reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.134, sc15
msgctxt "an7.72:15.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "an7.72:15.2"
msgid "katamaṃ nu kho varaṃ—yaṃ balavā puriso uddhampādaṃ adhosiraṃ gahetvā tattāya lohakumbhiyā pakkhipeyya ādittāya sampajjalitāya sajotibhūtāya—so tattha pheṇuddehakaṃ paccamāno sakimpi uddhaṃ gaccheyya sakimpi adho gaccheyya sakimpi tiriyaṃ gaccheyya, yaṃ vā khattiyamahāsālānaṃ vā brāhmaṇamahāsālānaṃ vā gahapatimahāsālānaṃ vā saddhādeyyaṃ vihāraṃ paribhuñjeyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Which is better—to have a strong man grab you, turn you upside down, and shove you in a red-hot copper pot, burning, blazing, and glowing, where you’re seared in boiling scum, and swept up and down and round and round. Or to enjoy the use of dwellings given in faith by well-to-do aristocrats or brahmins or householders?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.72:15.3"
msgid "“Etadeva, bhante, varaṃ—yaṃ khattiyamahāsālānaṃ vā brāhmaṇamahāsālānaṃ vā gahapatimahāsālānaṃ vā saddhādeyyaṃ vihāraṃ paribhuñjeyya, dukkhañhetaṃ, bhante, yaṃ balavā puriso uddhampādaṃ adhosiraṃ gahetvā tattāya lohakumbhiyā pakkhipeyya ādittāya sampajjalitāya sajotibhūtāya—so tattha pheṇuddehakaṃ paccamāno sakimpi uddhaṃ gaccheyya sakimpi adho gaccheyya sakimpi tiriyaṃ gaccheyyā”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, it would be much better to enjoy the use of dwellings given in faith by well-to-do aristocrats or brahmins or householders. For it would be painful to have a strong man grab you, turn you upside down, and shove you in a red-hot copper pot, burning, blazing, and glowing, where you’re seared in boiling scum, and swept up and down and round and round.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "an7.72:16.1"
msgid "“Ārocayāmi vo, bhikkhave, paṭivedayāmi vo, bhikkhave, yathā etadeva tassa varaṃ dussīlassa pāpadhammassa … pe … kasambujātassa yaṃ balavā puriso uddhampādaṃ adhosiraṃ gahetvā … pe … sakimpi tiriyaṃ gaccheyya. "
msgstr "“I declare this to you, mendicants, I announce this to you! It would be better for that unethical man to have a strong man grab him, turn him upside down, and shove him in a red-hot copper pot, burning, blazing, and glowing, where he’s seared in boiling scum, and swept up and down and round and round. "

msgctxt "an7.72:16.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an7.72:16.3"
msgid "Tatonidānañhi so, bhikkhave, maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ, na tveva tappaccayā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya. "
msgstr "Because that might result in death or deadly pain. But when his body breaks up, after death, it would not cause him to be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

msgctxt "an7.72:16.4"
msgid "Yañca kho so, bhikkhave, dussīlo pāpadhammo … pe … kasambujāto khattiyamahāsālānaṃ vā brāhmaṇamahāsālānaṃ vā gahapatimahāsālānaṃ vā saddhādeyyaṃ vihāraṃ paribhuñjati. Tañhi tassa, bhikkhave, hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati. (7) "
msgstr "But when such an unethical man enjoys the use of dwellings given in faith by well-to-do aristocrats or brahmins or householders, that brings him lasting harm and suffering. When his body breaks up, after death, he’s reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.135, sc17
msgctxt "an7.72:17.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "So you should train like this: "

#. VAR: yesañca → yesaṃ (?)
#. VAR: cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ → … parikkhārānaṃ (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an7.72:17.2"
msgid "‘yesañca mayaṃ paribhuñjāma cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ tesaṃ te kārā mahapphalā bhavissanti mahānisaṃsā, amhākañcevāyaṃ pabbajjā avañjhā bhavissati saphalā saudrayā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Our use of robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick shall be of great fruit and benefit for those who offered them. And our going forth will not be wasted, but will be fruitful and fertile.’ "

msgctxt "an7.72:17.3"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "That’s how you should train. "

msgctxt "an7.72:17.4"
msgid "‘attatthaṃ vā, bhikkhave, sampassamānena alameva appamādena sampādetuṃ; "
msgstr "Considering your own good, mendicants, is quite enough for you to persist with diligence. "

msgctxt "an7.72:17.5"
msgid "paratthaṃ vā, bhikkhave, sampassamānena alameva appamādena sampādetuṃ; "
msgstr "Considering the good of others is quite enough for you to persist with diligence. "

msgctxt "an7.72:17.6"
msgid "ubhayatthaṃ vā, bhikkhave, sampassamānena alameva appamādena sampādetun’”ti. "
msgstr "Considering the good of both is quite enough for you to persist with diligence.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
#. VAR: Idamavoca bhagavā → idamavoca bhagavā …pe… (mr)
msgctxt "an7.72:18.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

#. VAR: uggañchi → uggacchi (mr)
msgctxt "an7.72:18.2"
msgid "Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne saṭṭhimattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ uṇhaṃ lohitaṃ mukhato uggañchi. "
msgstr "And while this discourse was being spoken, sixty monks spewed hot blood from their mouths. "

msgctxt "an7.72:18.3"
msgid "Saṭṭhimattā bhikkhū sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattiṃsu: "
msgstr "Sixty mendicants rejected the training and returned to a lesser life, saying: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.72:18.4"
msgid "“sudukkaraṃ bhagavā, sudukkaraṃ bhagavā”ti. "
msgstr "“It’s too hard, Blessed One! It’s just too hard!” "

msgctxt "an7.72:18.5"
msgid "Saṭṭhimattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsūti. "
msgstr "And sixty monks were freed from defilements by not grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.72:18.6"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

